[quote name='Chakat Firepaw']It&#39;s a good thing we&#39;re only at 1.4 times pre-industrial levels of CO2. If we were at double, we would have about three degrees of warming locked in and that&#39;s about where we would get a oceanic CO2 release feedback loop and another event like the PETM.<br>
[/QUOTE]<br>
You mean the one that made mammals like us the dominant top-tier form of life on the planet? That one? Isn&#39;t that sort of like saying &#39;if you&#39;re not careful, Santa Claus will come?&#39;
